4.12pm: Jiminy Cricket, what a session that was! As ever, Steven Smith was at the centre of the action: imperious with the bat until roughed up by Jofra Archer, who stoked up the Babylonian fires during an electric spell. Smith was first struck on the arm, bringing up a duck egg-like bruise; then he was felled amid worrying scenes, taking a blow on the neck from another Archer bumper. Fortunately he was able to walk off, only to then return at the fall of the next wicket and get to within a couple of blows of a remarkable century. At the end of it all, England have an eight-run lead on first innings and the next session will be key in attempts to force a result. You can bet Australia will be fired up to back up Smith's bravery with the ball. Do England have a wobble in them? Find out with Gnasher shortly
